<TEXT>
flamboyant restaurateur peter langan unconscious 
since being burned in a fire at his home in october died wednesday 
night st andrews hospital at billericay said he was 47 
irishborn langan whose langans brasserie in londons west end 
was a favorite with show business personalities coowned the 
restaurant with actor michael caine and chef richard shepherd he 
also owned a restaurant in los angeles 
langan was burned when a fire broke out at 4 am on oct 21 at 
his home at alphamstone 50 miles northeast of london after what 
police called a serious domestic incident with his wife susan 46 
news reports at the time said mrs langan who broke her ankle 
jumping from a balcony had told langan she wanted to leave him 
shepherd said at the time that an oil heater in a bedroom 
accidentally started the blaze but the british domestic news agency 
press association said wednesday that police believe langan may have 
started the fire deliberately after an argument with mrs langan 
langan a former selfconfessed hardened drinker was remembered 
at langans brasserie for stunts such as crawling across the floor 
and biting customers ankles and putting out a fire in the kitchen 
with vintage champagne 
he was a great character and will be sadly missed said peter 
malva the manager of the business 
</TEXT>
