<TEXT>
police arrested 15 organizers of a 
human rights march banned by the government of president gen 
alfredo stroessner church radio reported wednesday 
the march for life set for saturday is to commemorate the 
40th anniversary of the united nations universal declaration of 
human rights organizers declared it will take place despite the 
arrests 
we have persuasive means to stop the march and i can assure 
you it will not take place interior minister sabino montanaro 
said 
but coorganizer miguel abdoon saguier said on dec 10 we 
will be in the streets and if the government represses us and beats 
us these violations will be used as proof against it before the 
united nations committee on human rights and the organization of 
american states 
the interior ministry issued a statement tuesday saying the 
government opposes the march on the grounds that participants 
include known agitators who are seeking to disturb the peace of 
the country 
domingo laino leader of the authentic liberal radical party and 
perhaps this south american nations most wellknown critic of the 
government was arrested tuesday night the roman catholic churchs 
radio caritas reported 
also arrested were fernando vera president of the febrerista 
revolutionary party ligia prieto president of the paraguayan 
womens union elsa mereles a leader of the nurses union at the 
national clinical hospital and three leaders of the committee of 
churches which represents catholics and protestants 
demonstrators intend to march seven blocks from the national 
cathedral to the offices of the united nations in downtown asuncion 
the march was organized by a group called the national 
convergence for human rights comprised of opposition political 
parties and unions 
stroessner 75 seized power in 1954 and has ruled since with the 
support of the army and the colorado party 
