praised websters reappointment saying the director had helped 
restore public confidence in the cia during a very troubling 
period 
last march webster told a congressional committee he had 
reorganized the spy agency to improve counterintelligence and 
strengthen security at us embassies 
webster who grew up in the st louis suburb of webster groves 
mo received a bachelors degree from amherst college and a law 
degree in 1949 from washington university in st louis 
he served briefly as us attorney for eastern missouri and was 
appointed to the us district court bench by president nixon in 
1971 and to the 8th us circuit court of appeals in 1973 
webster a widower has three children 
