someday shoppers at a mall may enter a computer 
booth to pay a parking ticket or utility bill register to vote or 
check on garbage pickup times municipal officials say 
the key thing is to make it easier for people to get 
information about their government at a place and time convenient to 
them kansas city mo city councilor john a sharp said tuesday 
we still operate at the convenience of the bureaucracy not at the 
convenience of citizens 
residents cant yet pay parking tickets or apply for building 
permits by computer but in kansas city charlotte nc and 
hillsborough county fla they can receive a wide array of 
electronic information about government services and operations 
the two cities and the county are taking part in a computerbased 
pilot program that gives people easier access to local government 
officials said at the national league of cities convention tueday 
the projects cost was not released 
computerized communications between residents and government may 
seem impersonal but officials said the technology is a convenient 
efficient way to provide more better information 
using equipment donated by international business machines inc 
the three jurisdictions made the information services available this 
year the project was organized by public technology inc of 
washington the leagues nonprofit research and development arm 
in kansas city computer kiosks with a color screen that displays 
information and pictures have been set up in two malls for about a 
year connected directly to city hall 
residents can touch a screen and get information on recreational 
events licenses and permits complaints about police traffic or 
trash pickup neighborhood services government meetings or city 
jobs the computers have averaged 700 touches daily and are on line 
15 hours a day 
in a survey of the computer users more than half said they had 
never been to city hall for the kind of information available in the 
computer during a onemonth period requests for information on 
recreational events totaled 1880 compared with 398 complaints 
