repressive measure passed by the government was celebrated by 
terrorists as a symptom of their success the bill represents 
further encroachment on the rights and liberties of all people of 
our country and a step further down the tragic path to a less 
democratic and less free society sheerman said 
the act allows suspected terrorists to be detained without charge 
for 48 hours although the government can extend that for five days 
and to bar suspects in northern ireland from entering mainland 
britain 
on monday night the commons approved a bill that would make all 
candidates for local and provincial assembly offices in northern 
