as nato 2 times as many tanks double the number of men and double 
the number of aircraft 
healey said the soviets no longer are a threat and that no soviet 
government even josef stalins ever intended to invade western 
europe 
the important thing now is we have the chance of working 
together with the russians to create stability and peace in 
europe he declared we ought to grab it with both hands 
paul rodgers an analyst at the department of peace studies in 
bradford northern england said gorbachev has the ulterior motive 
of sabotaging western agreement on modernizing nuclear forces nato 
has not yet agreed on what to do after intermediaterange missiles 
are withdrawn from europe under the ussoviet treaty 
it is going to make it much more difficult for nato to agree on 
a decision to modernize nuclear weapons rodgers said 
henry a kissinger national security adviser and secretary of 
