measures tremors on the basis of their visible effects an 
earthquake of 8 on the soviet scale is described in soviet reference 
works as destructive causing cracks on sharp slopes and in 
wet soils monuments are moved or turned over houses are 
considerably damaged 
the us geological survey said the earthquake was followed less 
than five minutes later by a moderate aftershock measuring 58 on 
the richter scale 
the moscow central seismic center put the epicenter 30 miles from 
leninakan it was felt in the armenian capital of yerevan 95 miles 
to the southeast as well as in georgia and azerbaijan soviet tv 
said 
because of violence between armenians and azerbaijanis more than 
