a woman opened fire in a battered womens shelter 
wednesday killing a shelter worker wounding two other people and 
barricading herself in a room for 90 minutes before police persuaded 
her to give up 
denver police said juanita whitaker 40 surrendered at the 
brandon center after an officer convinced her she would not be 
harmed and promised to buy her some hair curlers that she wanted 
when the shooting began mothers grabbed their small children and 
ran out into the falling snow without taking time to put on coats 
about 35 to 40 people were in the shelter at the time said dianna 
kunz president of volunteers of america colorado branch which 
operates the center 
whitaker was being held in the denver city jail without bond for 
investigation of firstdegree murder she was scheduled to be 
arraigned thursday 
police identified the dead woman as jeannie archuleta 24 of 
denver who had begun work at the shelter less than two months ago 
two people were in serious condition at denver general hospital 
said hospital spokeswoman lisa duchon ken sanchez 29 a shelter 
counselor was shot in the abdomen a 31yearold woman who was not 
identified because she was a shelter client suffered a leg wound 
police spokeswoman anne montoya said whitaker was despondent over 
personal problems and soon was going to have to leave the shelter 
where she had lived since nov 18 
