<TEXT>
the governing council of the international civil 
aviation organization decided wednesday to send a report on the 
downing of a iranian airliner by a us warship to an internal panel 
for review 
assad kotaite president of the 33country governing council 
said at the end of two days of closed meetings that some nations 
discussed generally condemning the act of shooting down a civilian 
aircraft 
but kotaite said the council reserved judgment on the incident 
until it hears back from the organizations air navigation 
commission at its next meeting in february 
he denied there was any discussion of condemning the united 
states for the downing of the iran air a300 airbus on july 3 in the 
persian gulf all 290 people aboard the plane were killed 
edmund stohr us representative to the united nations agency 
earlier told reporters there were a number of council members 
that felt that there should have been a condemnation 
kotaite said the condemnation of the use of force against 
civil aircraft was stated by a number of representatives now we 
postpone our action on the report until spring 
the iranian delegation has urged the council to censure the 
united states since a special meeting last july considered the 
downing of iran air flight 655 by the uss vincennes 
mahmood hajighasemali spokesman for the delegation told 
reporters that iran will wait for the commissions report but he 
said our people will not tolerate a further delay in the 
finalizing of the issue 
president reagan has promised compensation to families of the 
victims but the us has accepted no blame in the incident 
both the icao report which was officially released wednesday 
after being leaked last week and an earlier us defense department 
investigation found a series of events aboard the vincennes led the 
ships crew to erroneously believe the passenger plane was an 
attacking iranian f14 fighter 
the report said american warships in the persian gulf had no 
equipment that allowed them to monitor air traffic control 
frequencies they therefore had no way to hear radio transmissions 
between the iran air airbus and air traffic controllers it said 
the report said 11 warnings were issued to the jet before it was 
downed by two missiles from the vincennes but only one warning 
from another us ship in the area was coded specifically for the 
iran air flight that message came only about 40 seconds before the 
jet was destroyed 
the report says military units in hazardous situations should be 
provided with the means to monitor air traffic control frequencies 
and to communicate directly with civilian controllers it also 
recommends that military warnings be improved 
sending the report to the air navigation commission a 15person 
technical body follows an example set in 1983 when icao 
investigated the downing of a korean air lines boeing 747 by the 
soviet union all 269 people aboard were killed 
after that investigation the report was sent to the commission 
the icao council eventually refused to condemn the soviet union 
adopting instead a motion deploring the use of military force 
against civilian aircraft 
icao with 159 member countries sets standards for civil 
aviation and airline safety from its headquarters in montreal it 
can make recommendations that are not binding on its members 
