the holiday a time of games and giftgiving is sometimes 
regarded as a jewish counterpart of christmas and both signify a new 
start a fresh element of faith 
also without the precedent of hanukkah scholars point out that 
there presumably could be no christmas 
the jewish festival of lights celebrates an ancient turn of 
