<TEXT>
gaming whiz steve wynn stood in the 
sunbaked parking lot of his latest casino acquisition recently and 
enthused laughlin reminds me of what las vegas was 40 years ago 
wynn isnt alone in the attachment americas gaming giants have 
developed for this fastgrowing gambling community nestled along 
the scenic colorado river near the southern tip of nevada 
what once was a tiny bar and a handful of slot machines hidden at 
the end of an isolated road has been transformed into one of the 
premier growth areas in this booming gambling state 
giants of the hotelcasino industry such as holiday inn ramada 
hilton circus circus and golden nugget are clamoring to get a piece 
of the laughlin action 
the 1988 visitor count is expected to be up by onethird from the 
estimated 15 million a year ago casino revenues are forecast to 
surpass those of lake tahoe the no 3 market in the state after las 
vegas and reno in a year or two 
bolstered by balmy temperatures no vacancy signs abound 
throughout the winter months 
welcome snowbirds flashes a 20foothigh neon sign atop don 
laughlins riverside resort and casino the flagship of the 
evergrowing list of casino resorts here 
it was laughlin 57 who happened across this remote area while 
flying along the colorado river in a private plane in 1966 he 
spotted an outoftheway rundown bar and paid 225000 for the 
saloon a blackjack table a dozen slot machines and eight 
boardedup motel rooms four of which became the temporary home for 
the laughlin family 
giving the town his name wasnt laughlins idea when postal 
officials asked for a name for the patch of real estate 20 years 
ago laughlin suggested casino noting a town on nevadas northern 
border was named jackpot 
the inspector of irish descent balked at the idea and opted for 
laughlin calling it a good irish name 
for many years don laughlins motelcasino was the only game in 
town because of the remote location and competition from las vegas 
95 miles to the northwest 
the town came alive in the early 1980s with gaming revenues 
climbing to 41 million by 1981 doubling to 80 million by 1983 and 
hitting 2424 million in 1987 
lake tahoe recorded 3095 million in gaming revenues in 1987 
while reno had 5525 million and las vegas hit 2237 billion 
location plays a major role in laughlins stunning growth 
the town is about 280 miles the same distance as las vegas 
from most southern california cities the markets that feed southern 
nevadas voracious appetite for gamblers 
gaming giants sat on the sidelines for years while land 
speculators touted the area as the next las vegas 
suddenly the major players began to make their move two years 
ago when the town had 1600 hotel rooms today laughlin has 4118 
rooms at nine resorts with 3000 new rooms to be completed in the 
next 12 to 18 months 
the first major player to move here was circus circus the 
familythemed gaming empire with operations in las vegas and reno 
the company built an 80 million 1238room hotel and casino in the 
shape of a mississippi riverboat the facility with smokestacks 
soaring 21 stories high and paddlewheels 90 feet in diameter 
dominates the waterfront 
not since noah has anyone built such a big boat in the middle 
of the desert quipped bill paulos the hotels general manager 
when the company opened the facility on a blistering july 1 1987 
last june ramada set up shop across busy casino center drive 
the main drag that was a sleepy twolane street six years ago and 
now carries four lanes of cars and campers bumpertobumper around 
the clock 
the 60 million ramada express features an early americana 
railroad theme with a steam engine train toting passengers around 
the 406room hotel and casino 
harrahs the gaming arm of holiday inn opened the mexicanstyle 
del rio in july the 65 million 446room resort became the ninth 
hotelcasino in laughlin 
wynn who owns the golden nugget in downtown las vegas and is 
building a 550 million resort on the las vegas strip said laughlin 
couldnt be ignored any longer 
he bought the nevada club casino from del webb corp for 40 
