<TEXT>
the federal governments first experiment in 
taking over a mobrun union ended wednesday with one of the nations 
largest teamsters locals electing officers allied to the corrupt 
regime ousted four years ago 
i think its a real disaster for the future of the labor 
movement said clyde summers a labor law expert at the 
university of pennsylvania 
but other labor observers said the very existence of a 
legitimately contested election at local 560 justified the interim 
rule by a courtappointed trustee that preceded the vote 
newcomers represent the revitalization of the political process 
in this local said linda kaboolian a fellow at harvard 
universitys kennedy school of government who has researched the 
local 560 trusteeship for a year 
that they didnt win isnt the final word on the future of 
local 560 she said 
the election also could affect the justice departments suit 
against the international brotherhood of teamsters which seeks to 
oust the parent unions board and establish a trustee to keep out 
corruption and establish elections 
certainly its a good example of a potential backlash against a 
trusteeship said goldberg 
the teamsters for liberty ticket which includes two relatives of 
ousted officers of local 560 captured 65 percent of 4530 ballots 
counted tuesday and early wednesday in balloting that brought an 
unusually high turnout among the locals 7600 members 
teamsters for liberty opposed the courtappointed trusteeship 
which was imposed in 1986 after us district judge harold a 
ackerman found in a justice department lawsuit that organized crime 
had ruled the union citybased local for more than a quartercentury 
he ordered removal of the locals executive board 
ballots were mailed on november in the locals first contested 
election in 23 years 
danny sciarra and mark sheridan led the winning slate to become 
the new president and vice president 
they are relatives of former officers michael sciarra and joseph 
sheridan who this fall were barred from running because of ties to 
the old leaders the new officers have said they will rely on and 
consult with their kin in running the union 
the trustee edwin h stier a former prosecutor will monitor 
the local for at least three months after which the new 
sevenmember board must report to ackerman on its activities the 
judge also kept indefinite jurisdiction over the board 
attorney harvey weissbard who represented michael sciarra and 
joseph sheridan said the votes results were a clear vindication of 
his clients and a rejection of the trusteeship 
i think clearly the vast majority of the members really did 
not appreciate having the trusteeship thrust upon them he said 
i just think that the whole concept is illconceived 
