in reaction to gorbachevs remarks at the united nations and partly 
on expectations which were later confirmed that a large export 
offer was in the works 
other grain and soybean futures finished mostly lower 
gorbachevs remarks stirred speculation that the soviet union 
would use money saved through reduced defense spending to buy more 
us grain said john frazier a grainmarket specialist with 
balfour maclaine corp in chicago 
after the close the agriculture department announced that it had 
targeted china for 1 million metric tons of us wheat at subsidized 
prices and that 100000 metric tons of subsidized wheat had been 
sold to morocco 
