shares of texaco inc surged in active trading 
wednesday boosted by intensifying speculation that financier carl 
icahn might be planning a new effort to gain control of the oil 
giant 
the speculation catapulted texaco 2 to 51 on the new york stock 
exchange its third consecutive rise the jump made a major 
contribution to wednesdays 427 point gain in the dow jones average 
of 30 industrials which closed at 215363 
icahn the owner and chairman of trans world airlines inc holds 
a 148 percent stake in texaco last june he lost a proxy fight to 
oust the oil companys top management 
usa today financial columnist dan dorfman reported monday that an 
unidentified party recently approached icahn about selling his 
texaco stake dorfman also said he picked up solid reports that 
another party possibly the one that approached icahn has been 
quietly accumulating texaco shares 
the speculation mounted when the new york times suggested in 
tuesdays editions that icahn is in talks with another party to 
launch a new takeover battle for texaco 
the times story quoted unidentified oil industry experts as 
saying the deal under discussion would eventually give icahn the 
opportunity to sell his texaco stake the other partner reportedly 
would build up a separate block close to 8 percent or 9 percent of 
the companys outstanding shares 
icahn did not return a call from the associated press seeking 
comment wednesday 
he told dow jones professional investor report that he has no 
current intention to sell his texaco shares and continues to believe 
the companys stock is undervalued he also indicated that he may 
purchase additional texaco stock from time to time based on market 
conditions 
a trader with bear stearns amp co told the dow jones report 
wednesday that his brokerage firm has been buying texaco shares and 
he named salomon brothers inc as another buyer 
