<TEXT>
general motors corp is recalling about 85000 
1988 pontiac lemans cars and about 4000 1988 oldsmobile cutlass 
supreme and pontiac grand prix models for faulty safety belt buckles 
and parking brake cables 
the automaker said wednesday it is unaware of any accidents or 
injuries caused by the defects which have surfaced on some models 
equipped with manual transmissions 
on the lemans vehicles seat belt buckles may appear to be 
latched when they are not gm said 
on some cutlass supreme and grand prix cars the parking brake 
may not work because the cable is improperly connected 
dealers will make inspections and repairs free of charge to car 
owners the automaker said 
